Title : Bardot (English band)
Text : {{distinguish|Bardot (Australian band)|Bardo (band)}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}}
{{Use British English|date=June 2016}}
'''Bardot''' were a trio of singer/songwriters whose sound was sometimes compared to [[Crosby, Stills & Nash]] and [[Eagles (band)|The Eagles]]. The band released 'Rockin In Rhythm' in 1978 on the RCA label, a collection of polished folk rock songs heavy on melody and complex harmonies.<ref name=MusicStack>{{cite web|title=Rockin In Rhythm @ MusicStack|url=http://www.musicstack.com/discography/bardot+(3)/rocking+in+rhythm/r1709687|work=MusicStack DB|accessdate=28 April 2014}}</ref> Three singles were also released, the debut ''Witchfire'' hitting number 14 in the Dutch charts.<ref name=Witchfire_Top40>{{cite web|title=Witchfire Top 40 Hit|url=http://www.top40.nl/bardot/bardot-witchfire_18794#songtekst|website=www.top40.nl|accessdate=20 August 2014}}</ref><ref name=Witchfire_Top40_detail>{{cite web|title=Witchfire Chart Position 14|url=http://www.top40.nl/pdf/1978/tipparade-19780701.pdf|website=www.top40.nl|accessdate=20 August 2014}}</ref>
<br />
Ray McRiner on guitar and vocals, was also known for his compositions, arrangement, vocal and instrumental work with [[The Sweet|Sweet]], and as touring guitarist for the band.<ref name=RM1>{{cite web|title=Ray McRiner credits. All Music database.|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/ray-mcriner-mn0001218108|work=Writing, arrangement, vocal and instrumental credits for work with The Sweet|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=RM2>{{cite web|title=Ray McRiner credits. Artist Direct database. |url=http://www.artistdirect.com/artist/credits/ray-mcriner/466719|work=Writing, arrangement, vocal and instrumental credits for work with The Sweet|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=RM3>{{cite web|title=Ray McRiner credits. Discogs database. |url=http://www.discogs.com/artist/1408848-Ray-McRiner|work=Writing, arrangement, vocal and instrumental credits for work with The Sweet|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=RM4>{{cite web|title=Ray McRiner in Sweet article. Musicmight Rock database|url=http://www.rockdetector.com/artist/uk/sweet|work=Live touring credits for work with The Sweet|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=RM5>{{cite web|title=Ray McRiner in Sweet article. Signal2 radio station database |url=http://www.signal2.co.uk/music/artist/sweet/bio/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140429091149/http://www.signal2.co.uk/music/artist/sweet/bio/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=29 April 2014 |work=Live touring credits for work with The Sweet |accessdate=30 April 2014 }}</ref><ref name=RM6>{{cite web|title=Ray McRiner in Sweet article. Classic Rock Bottom database|url=http://classic-rock-bottom.ning.com/group/sweet|work=Live touring and composer credits for work with The Sweet|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> 
<br />
Laurie Andrew on guitar and vocals, was also a successful solo recording artist in his own right with the single ''I'll Never Love Anyone Anymore'', a top of the Pops appearance,<ref name=LA4>{{cite web|title=www.dailymotion.com video archive|url=http://www.dailymotion.com/video/xi61pg_laurie-andrew-i-ll-never-love-anyone-anymore-1976_shortfilms|work=Video of Laurie Andrew on top of The Pops|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=LA5>{{cite web|title=pro-labs.imdb.com|url=https://pro-labs.imdb.com/name/nm4401423/|work=IMDB entry for BBC TV program Top of the Pops appearance|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> along with composition and vocal credits for work with [[Sir Cliff Richard]], [[Boney M]], Traks, Gianco, Keith Forsey (session musician for [[Harold Faltermeyer]] and [[Giorgio Moroder]] among others), and [[Lesley Duncan]].<ref name=LA1>{{cite web|title=Laurie Andrew credits. All Music database|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/laurie-andrew-mn0001249433|work=Writing and vocal credits for work with Sir Cliff Richard, Bardot, and Leslie Duncan.|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=LA2>{{cite web|title=Laurie Andrew credits. 45cat vinyl seven inch single online archive|url=http://www.45cat.com/record/arista34|work=Writing, performance credits for solo single|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref name=LA3>{{cite web|title=Laurie Andrew credits. Discogs database|url=http://www.discogs.com/artist/859459-Laurie-Andrew?type=Credits|work=Writing, performance credits|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref>

== Personnel ==
* Ray McRiner - composer, guitar, vocals
* Laurie Andrew - composer, vocals 
* [[Chris Bradford (rock musician)|Chris Bradford]] - composer, vocals
* [[Pip Williams]] - producer

